<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Palaearctic species. Recorded in the Czech Republic, Finland, Germany, Slovakia, Switzerland and Russia (ER). New record for Romania.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="biology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
Very rare species with early flight period. The individuals are collected only in IV and V and were almost exclusively females. Larval biology and host fungus are unknown. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Tkoč">Tkoc</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Barták">Bartak</normalizedToken>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species in numbers from a pyramidal (emergence) trap baited with dead wood.
</paragraph>
